* Folio 1 (i.e., leaf) [[recto and verso|recto]] : [[Genesis creation narrative|Creation]] of [[heaven]] and [[earth]] (''[[Book of Genesis|Genesis]]'', 1: 1-5).
* Folio 1 [[Recto and verso|verso]] : Creation of the [[water]]s and the [[firmament]] (''Genesis'', 1: 6-8).
* Folio 2 recto : Creation of the [[bird]]s and [[fish]]es (''Genesis'', 1: 20-23).
* Folio 2 verso : Creation of the [[animal]]s (''Genesis'', 1: 24-25).
* Folio 3 recto : Creation of [[man]] (''Genesis'', 1: 26-28, 31; 2: 1-2).
* Folio 5 recto : [[Adam (Bible)|Adam]] names the [[animal]]s ([[Isidore of Seville]], ''[[Etymologiae]]'', Book XII, i, 1-2).
* Folio 5 verso : [[Animal]] (''Animal'') (Isidore of Seville, ''Etymologiae'', Book XII, i, 3)
* Folio 5 verso : [[Quadruped]] (''Quadrupes'') (Isidore of Seville, ''Etymologiae'', Book XII, i, 4)
* Folio 5 verso : [[Livestock]] (''Pecus'') (Isidore of Seville, ''Etymologiae'', Book XII, i, 5-6)
* Folio 5 verso : [[Pack animal|Beast of burden]] (''Iumentum'') (Isidore of Seville, ''Etymologiae'', Book XII, i, 7)
* Folio 5 verso : [[Herd]] (''Armentum'') (Isidore of Seville, ''Etymologiae'', Book XII, i, 8)

